♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS ♪

01:43.886 --> 01:46.671
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:08.345 --> 02:09.955
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

02:11.261 --> 02:13.481
-FIRE DEPARTMENT
SAVES 20 LIVES.

02:14.264 --> 02:16.658
BET YOU IT DOESN'T EVEN MENTION
THAT WE PUT OF THE BLAZE

02:16.788 --> 02:17.789
BEFORE THEY EVEN GOT THERE.

02:18.703 --> 02:21.010
-SOME OF US AREN'T IN
THIS FOR THE GLORY, MITCH.

02:21.837 --> 02:23.012
-JUST THE SOOT, RIGHT?

02:23.143 --> 02:24.100
-[LAUGHS] RIGHT.

02:28.452 --> 02:31.499
-THERE'S SOMETHING UP AHEAD
IN THE WATER, ABOUT 2:00.

02:31.629 --> 02:32.413
-HANG ON.

02:32.543 --> 02:34.806
[BOAT ENGINE REVS]

02:39.637 --> 02:41.509
-IT'S A DOG.

02:42.031 --> 02:44.164
-TAKE THE WHEEL,
BROOKE. GET ME CLOSE.

02:49.256 --> 02:50.561
-RIGHT ABOUT TWO.

02:53.303 --> 02:55.392
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

03:11.669 --> 03:14.237
-COME HERE, PAL.
I GOTCHA, I GOTCHA.

03:15.020 --> 03:17.980
OKAY. YEAH.

03:19.068 --> 03:20.025
HANG ON.

03:22.593 --> 03:23.420
HANG ON.

03:25.683 --> 03:26.945
-COME HERE, BABY.

03:28.251 --> 03:29.470
[GRUNTS]

03:31.559 --> 03:32.734
I GOT HIM, MITCH.
-OKAY.

03:34.997 --> 03:35.911
-GOT HIM?

03:38.914 --> 03:40.132
COME ON, BOY.

03:40.742 --> 03:41.786
GOT HIM?

03:51.361 --> 03:52.797
-EASY. EASY.

03:53.537 --> 03:56.627
-THERE'S NO TAG ON THE COLLAR.
MUST'VE FALLEN OFF A BOAT.

03:57.889 --> 04:00.718
-WE'RE TEN MILES OUT.
THERE'S NO BOATS OUT HERE.

04:02.067 --> 04:03.721
-IT'S AMAZING HE'S STILL ALIVE.

04:04.244 --> 04:06.289
-HE WON'T BE FOR LONG.
HYPOTHERMIA'S SETTING IN.

04:06.420 --> 04:08.596
COME ON. GET US BACK
TO HEADQUARTERS.

04:09.858 --> 04:11.642
[BOAT ENGINE CRANKS]

04:13.035 --> 04:15.342
[BOAT ENGINE REVS]

04:23.698 --> 04:27.005
-NOW, EDDIE, I'M GONNA
ASK YOU A COUPLE QUESTIONS.

04:27.528 --> 04:29.094
SO JUST TRY AND FOLLOW ALONG.

04:29.747 --> 04:31.532
OKAY.

04:31.662 --> 04:33.534
"YOU OBJECT TO YOUR GIRLFRIEND
FLIRTING WITH OTHER GUYS:

04:33.664 --> 04:35.318
NEVER, SOMETIMES, ALWAYS?"

04:36.798 --> 04:37.625
-SOMETIMES.

04:38.452 --> 04:39.279
-SOMETIMES?

04:40.192 --> 04:41.368
-MOST OF THE TIME.

04:42.891 --> 04:44.371
FINE, ALWAYS. ALWAYS.

04:45.285 --> 04:47.939
-[SCOFFS] OKAY, LET'S SEE.

04:48.070 --> 04:50.812
"YOU AND YOUR GIRLFRIEND
CRY AT THE SAME MOVIE:

04:50.942 --> 04:52.640
NEVER, SOMETIMES, ALWAYS?"

04:53.249 --> 04:55.556
-[SCOFFS] WHO WRITES THIS
STUFF? IT'S OBVIOUSLY NOT A MAN.

04:55.686 --> 04:56.774
-WHAT?

04:56.905 --> 04:57.993
-SOMETIMES.

04:59.473 --> 05:01.431
-EDDIE, YOU HAVE NEVER ONCE
CRIED AT A MOVIE WITH ME.

05:01.562 --> 05:03.041
-FINE. NEVER.

05:05.870 --> 05:07.263
-OKAY.

05:07.394 --> 05:09.439
-"YOU ARE THE ONE
WHO PLANS THE DATES:

05:09.570 --> 05:11.311
NEVER, SOMETIMES, ALWAYS?"

05:12.094 --> 05:14.792
-ME GET TO PLAN ONE
OF OUR DATES? NEVER.

05:15.663 --> 05:17.447
-COME ON, EDDIE.

05:17.578 --> 05:18.840
YOU JUST GOT US TICKETS TO GO
TO THE BALL GAME LAST WEEK.

05:18.970 --> 05:20.363
-WHICH WE GAVE
TO MITCH AND HOBIE

05:20.494 --> 05:21.843
BECAUSE WE HAD THE
CHARITY BENEFIT.

05:21.973 --> 05:23.932
MY ANSWER REMAINS NEVER.

05:24.062 --> 05:25.368
-YOU'RE STILL MAD
ABOUT THAT, AREN'T YOU?

05:25.499 --> 05:26.804
I KNEW IT! YOU'RE STILL MAD.

05:26.935 --> 05:28.763
-SHAUNI, WE ALWAYS
DO WHAT YOU WANT.

05:29.807 --> 05:31.722
-WE ALWAYS HAVE FUN, EDDIE.

05:31.853 --> 05:33.681
-OH, FUN. RIGHT.

05:35.378 --> 05:38.990
LET'S SEE. CHARITY BENEFITS.

05:39.643 --> 05:41.428
OOH, HEY,

05:41.558 --> 05:44.082
HOW ABOUT THOSE
LITTLE TEENY-WEENY
BINOCULARS AT THE OPERA?

05:44.213 --> 05:46.128
AND OH, HEY, LET'S NOT FORGET
ABOUT THE SEVEN DIFFERENT

05:46.258 --> 05:48.522
KNIVES AND SPOONS
AT DINNERTIME, HUH?

05:48.652 --> 05:51.089
-I GUESS WE HAVE DIFFERENT
IDEA ABOUT WHAT'S FUN.

05:51.612 --> 05:53.657
I GUESS WE HAVE REAL DIFFERENT
IDEAS ABOUT A LOT OF THINGS.

05:53.788 --> 05:55.529
-WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSE TO MEAN?

05:55.659 --> 05:57.487
-IT MEANS WE JUST SCORED A
TEN ON THE COMPATIBILITY TEST.

05:57.618 --> 05:58.749
-TEN? TEN COULD BE GOOD.

05:58.880 --> 06:00.272
-NOT WHEN IT'S
OUT OF 100.

06:00.925 --> 06:02.666
-OH. WELL, SO WHAT?

06:02.797 --> 06:05.365
WHO CARES WHAT SOME
STUPID TEST SAYS ANYWAY?

06:05.495 --> 06:07.192
-EDDIE, THIS TEST
IS NOT THE POINT.

06:07.323 --> 06:09.238
THE POINT IS THAT WE
HAVE SO MANY DIFFERENCES.

06:09.369 --> 06:11.849
YOU OBVIOUSLY HAVE A LOT OF
RESENTMENT ABOUT THE THINGS

06:11.980 --> 06:13.111
THAT I LIKE FOR
US TO DO TOGETHER.

06:13.242 --> 06:14.199
THAT'S THE POINT.

06:14.983 --> 06:16.941
I JUST FEEL LIKE WE'RE
SO DIFFERENT, YOU KNOW?

06:17.072 --> 06:18.290
AND MAYBE WE NEED TO--

06:18.421 --> 06:19.422
-WHAT?

06:19.553 --> 06:20.510
-MAYBE WE JUST NEED SOME SPACE.

06:23.121 --> 06:24.166
-OH, COME ON.

06:25.472 --> 06:26.342
HEY!

06:28.823 --> 06:31.129
[SOMBER MUSIC]

06:35.307 --> 06:38.180
-HEY, PAL. YOU HUNGRY?

06:41.879 --> 06:43.881
EASY, EASY, EASY. TAKE IT EASY.

06:44.621 --> 06:46.101
-HOW'S OUR PATIENT DOING?

06:46.231 --> 06:47.624
-WELL, HE'S DEFINITELY
OFF THE CRITICAL LIST

06:47.755 --> 06:49.104
AND TAKING NOURISHMENT.

06:49.234 --> 06:51.149
-WE'VE CHECKED THE
POUNDS, SHELTERS,

06:51.280 --> 06:53.064
NO MISSING DOG FITTING
HIS DESCRIPTION.

06:53.891 --> 06:57.460
YOU SWEET THING. DON'T
WORRY, WE'LL FIND YOUR OWNER.

06:57.591 --> 06:59.897
-WE COULD TAKE HIS
PICTURE, XEROX SOME FLIERS,

07:00.028 --> 07:01.421
AND DISTRIBUTE
THOUGHT THE MARINA.

07:02.422 --> 07:03.597
STILL GOT YOUR CAMERA WITH YOU?

07:03.727 --> 07:05.033
YEAH.

07:05.163 --> 07:06.687
YEAH, IT'S IN MY
LOCKER. I'LL GO GET IT.

07:06.817 --> 07:07.644
-GREAT!

07:08.515 --> 07:09.559
-WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO WITH HIM

07:09.690 --> 07:10.995
UNTIL WE FIND HIS OWNER, MITCH?

07:11.735 --> 07:13.302
-I DUNNO, BUT HE'S A GOOD
LOOKING DOG, ISN'T HE?

07:13.433 --> 07:14.303
COME HERE, PAL.

07:18.481 --> 07:19.264
[DOG GROWLS]

07:19.395 --> 07:21.832
AH, MAYBE I'LL JUST UM,

07:21.963 --> 07:23.443
MAYBE I'LL JUST TAKE
HIM HOME WITH ME.

07:24.444 --> 07:26.402
MAYBE HE'LL TAKE ME HOME HERE.

07:28.970 --> 07:33.191
-GRACIE, DON'T EVER GIVE GEORGE
A COMPATIBILITY TEST, HUH?

07:44.072 --> 07:48.163
[PHONE DIALS]

07:48.293 --> 07:50.861
-ANSWER MATE, NICOLE
SPEAKING. HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

07:51.906 --> 07:55.387
-IT'S EDDIE. HOW YOU
DOING NICOLE? NUMBER 1007.

07:55.518 --> 07:56.911
-HI, EDDIE.

07:57.041 --> 07:59.043
HOW'S MY FAVORITE
LIFEGUARD DOING TODAY?

07:59.827 --> 08:03.178
-WELL, LET'S JUST SAY IT'S
NICE TO HEAR A FRIENDLY VOICE.

08:03.787 --> 08:04.875
-YOU SOUND
A LITTLE TENSE.

08:05.876 --> 08:07.008
-I'VE HAD BETTER DAYS.

08:08.096 --> 08:09.619
SO WHAT DO YOU GOT FOR ME?

08:09.750 --> 08:12.361
-MITCH CALLED HE WANTS
YOU TO WORK TOWER 18 TODAY.

08:12.883 --> 08:13.667
-OH, YEAH? WHAT SHIFT?

08:13.797 --> 08:15.059
-TWO TO SEVEN.

08:15.190 --> 08:16.844
I WISH I WORKED AT THE BEACH.

08:16.974 --> 08:19.586
I'D LOVE TO BE THERE AT SUNSET.

08:19.716 --> 08:22.371
IT SOUNDS SO SEXY.

08:23.154 --> 08:26.462
THE SUNLIGHT OFF THE
WAVES, COOL BREEZE.

08:27.332 --> 08:30.118
ENJOY IT, EDDIE. BYE.

08:30.771 --> 08:31.598
-BYE.

08:41.216 --> 08:44.087
[GRUNTS]

08:54.142 --> 08:55.230
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

08:57.449 --> 08:58.973
-HEY, DO WE A FAVOR,
WILL YA? WATCH HIM.

08:59.103 --> 09:00.235
I GOTTA CHECK THE
TOWER ASSIGNMENTS.

09:00.365 --> 09:01.541
-WHERE'D HE COME FROM?

09:03.586 --> 09:05.588
HEY. HOW YOU DOING?

09:06.807 --> 09:08.025
CAN YOU SIT, HUH?

09:08.722 --> 09:10.550
HEY, THAT'S A GOOD TRICK.

09:12.290 --> 09:13.161
-HI.

09:13.988 --> 09:14.945
HEY, EDDIE. CAN WE TALK?

09:16.033 --> 09:16.904
[CLEARS THROAT]

09:17.992 --> 09:20.385
PLEASE STOP IGNORING ME. YOU'RE
REALLY BEING UNREASONABLE.

09:20.516 --> 09:22.083
-I'M BEING UNREASONABLE?

09:23.606 --> 09:26.478
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU JUST
ADD THAT TO THE LIST?

09:28.437 --> 09:30.265
-SHAUNI, I WILL WAIT
FOR YOU OUTSIDE, OKAY?

09:31.092 --> 09:33.442
EDDIE, IT'S BEEN REAL
GOOD TO MEET YOU.

09:33.573 --> 09:34.748
-YEAH.

09:34.878 --> 09:35.705
-I THINK I'M GOING
TO LIKE IT HERE.

09:40.928 --> 09:41.929
-WELL, I GOTTA GO.

09:43.147 --> 09:44.540
-OH YEAH, YEAH.

09:44.671 --> 09:45.585
YOU WOULDN'T WANT TO
KEEP DEREK WAITING.

09:51.199 --> 09:52.592
YOU KNOW, TWO CAN
PLAY THAT GAME.

09:53.462 --> 09:54.332
AIN'T THAT RIGHT, BUD?

09:55.769 --> 10:00.425
HEY, WHY DON'T YOU UH,
WATCH YOURSELF, HUH?

10:07.171 --> 10:09.913
[PHONE DIALS]

10:10.044 --> 10:12.568
-ANSWER MATE. NICOLE
SPEAKING. HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

10:12.699 --> 10:14.178
-HEY, NICOLE. IT'S--

10:14.309 --> 10:15.832
-EDDIE. HI.

10:17.791 --> 10:20.837
-HI. UH, GOT ANY MESSAGES?

10:20.968 --> 10:22.447
-NOTHING SO FAR.

10:25.625 --> 10:30.760
-LISTEN, NICOLE, I'M WORKING
TOWER 18 FROM TWO TO SEVEN.

10:30.891 --> 10:32.414
-I KNOW.

10:32.544 --> 10:35.635
THERE'S SUPPOSE TO BE A
BEAUTIFUL SUNSET TONIGHT.

10:37.071 --> 10:38.463
-WHY DON'T YOU COME DOWN
AND WATCH IT WITH ME?

10:44.295 --> 10:46.036
-IT'S AMAZING. HOW
DID YOU DO THAT?

10:46.776 --> 10:48.038
-GOTTA LET HIM KNOW
YOU MEAN BUSINESS.

10:51.346 --> 10:52.216
-LET'S GO!

10:54.610 --> 10:55.829
-HERE YOU GO.

10:56.438 --> 10:59.049
LISTEN, IF YOU RECOGNIZE
THIS DOG OR IT'S OWNER,

10:59.876 --> 11:03.532
WOULD YOU PLEASE CALL BAYWATCH
HEADQUARTERS, LET US KNOW?

11:03.663 --> 11:05.099
NUMBERS AT THE
BOTTOM OF THE PAGE.

11:06.013 --> 11:07.710
OKAY? THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

11:07.841 --> 11:09.190
-BYE.
-UH HUH.

11:13.411 --> 11:15.631
[BEACHGOERS TALKING
IN BACKGROUND]

11:37.914 --> 11:40.264
[PHONE RINGS]

11:41.483 --> 11:42.527
-TOWER 19.

11:42.658 --> 11:44.312
-SHAUNI? EDDIE.

11:45.269 --> 11:46.706
JUST WANTED TO LET YOU KNOW

11:46.836 --> 11:47.489
I WON'T BE GOING BACK
TO HEADQUARTERS TONIGHT.

11:47.619 --> 11:48.708
-OH, WHY NOT?

11:49.317 --> 11:50.622
-GOT PLANS.

11:50.753 --> 11:51.841
-WITH WHO?

11:51.972 --> 11:53.974
6-DOESN'T MATTER. SEE YOU LATER.

12:04.549 --> 12:05.420
-HI, EDDIE.

12:08.336 --> 12:09.729
[GIGGLES]

12:11.426 --> 12:12.514
-NICOLE?

12:12.644 --> 12:14.298
[GIGGLES]

12:28.443 --> 12:31.185
-I CAME DOWN A LITTLE
EARLY. I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.

12:31.315 --> 12:32.447
-OH, NOT AT ALL.

12:33.187 --> 12:34.579
-OKAY, GREAT! I'LL
SET EVERYTHING UP.

12:34.710 --> 12:37.060
-WELL, UH, ACTUALLY,
NICOLE, I WAS--

12:37.669 --> 12:39.367
I'M STARVING AND I WAS
REALLY KINDA HOPING

12:39.497 --> 12:40.760
MAYBE WE COULD GO OUT
AND GET SOMETHING TO EAT.

12:41.717 --> 12:43.980
-BUT EDDIE, THE SUNSET.

12:46.766 --> 12:48.724
OF COURSE, THERE IS ALWAYS
CANDLELIGHT. [GIGGLES]

12:49.290 --> 12:50.552
-THAT'S RIGHT.

12:51.553 --> 12:52.684
[HORN HONKS]

12:59.039 --> 13:02.042
-HEY, EDDIE. YOU
HAVE A GOOD TIME.

13:12.095 --> 13:16.012
-UM, I'VE GOTTA CLOSE
UP MY TOWER AND CHANGE.

13:16.143 --> 13:18.232
-OH, OH, OKAY. YOU WANT
ME TO GO DOWN THERE?

13:18.362 --> 13:19.146
-THAT WOULD BE GREAT.

13:19.276 --> 13:20.364
-OKAY.
-YEAH.

13:20.495 --> 13:21.801
I'LL, I'LL HUSTLE IT UP.

13:21.931 --> 13:23.367
-OKAY, I'LL SEE YOU IN A BIT.
-OKAY.

13:31.419 --> 13:35.727
[LIGHT, UPLIFTING MUSIC]

13:54.311 --> 13:55.356
-COME ON, COME ON.

13:56.400 --> 13:57.401
HEY, HOBESTER!

13:58.881 --> 14:00.709
COME ON DOWN. I GOT
SOMEONE I WANT YOU TO MEET.

14:03.233 --> 14:05.583
-DAD! DAD, A DOG!

14:06.280 --> 14:07.150
WHERE'D YOU GET HIM?

14:07.281 --> 14:08.282
-ISN'T HE A BEAUT?

14:08.848 --> 14:10.588
I RESCUED HIM OFF SAN
PEDRO THIS MORNING.

14:10.719 --> 14:12.721
WE'RE GONNA TAKE CARE OF HIM
UNTIL WE CAN FIND HIS OWNERS.

14:13.243 --> 14:15.811
-YOU RESCUED HIM? THAT
MEANS YOU'RE RESPONSIBLE.

14:15.942 --> 14:18.988
-RESPONSIBLE TO FIND
HIS OWNER, THAT'S ALL.

14:19.119 --> 14:20.424
-CAN'T WE KEEP HIM?

14:20.555 --> 14:21.904
-HOBESTER, I KNOW HOW
MUCH YOU'RE LOVE A DOG,

14:22.035 --> 14:23.036
BUT HE'S NOT OURS.

14:23.166 --> 14:24.559
-BUT HE'S SUCH A GREAT DOG!

14:24.689 --> 14:26.778
-AND I KNOW SOMEBODY
MISSES HIM VERY MUCH.

14:27.562 --> 14:29.129
LOOK, I DON'T WANT YOU
TO GET TOO ATTACHED HERE

14:29.259 --> 14:30.913
BECAUSE WHEN HE LEAVES,
YOU'RE GONNA GET REAL UPSET.

14:31.783 --> 14:33.220
-I WON'T. COME ON, BOY.

14:34.003 --> 14:36.353
-OH, SAND EVERYWHERE!

14:36.963 --> 14:39.139
-HEY, DAD, I'M
GONNA NAME HIM SANDY.

14:39.269 --> 14:41.619
-OH. GREAT!

14:44.013 --> 14:46.537
[PATRONS CHATTING,
GLASSES CLINKING]

14:50.846 --> 14:51.934
-SO EDDIE, WHAT'S GOOD HERE?

14:52.804 --> 14:54.458
-OH, EVERY--

14:54.589 --> 14:56.286
EVERYTHING. EVERY--

14:56.417 --> 14:57.679
EVERYTHING IS GOOD.

14:57.809 --> 14:59.072
IT'S UH, EVERYTHING
IS REAL GOOD.

15:00.247 --> 15:01.813
-I'VE EMBARRASSED
YOU, HAVEN'T I?

15:05.078 --> 15:06.470
-NO, NICOLE. I--

15:06.601 --> 15:08.037
-EDDIE, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO SAY ANYTHING.

15:08.168 --> 15:09.604
I KNOW I EMBARRASSED
YOU ON THE BEACH TODAY

15:09.734 --> 15:10.561
IN FRONT OF YOUR FRIENDS,

15:11.475 --> 15:13.216
AND I'M EMBARRASSING
YOU RIGHT NOW.

15:14.174 --> 15:16.219
YOU'VE NEVER BEEN TO THIS
RESTAURANT BEFORE, HAVE YOU?

15:20.397 --> 15:22.660
-NO. NO, NICOLE, I HAVEN'T.

15:23.792 --> 15:27.013
BUT YOU DIDN'T EMBARRASS
ME. I EMBARRASS ME.

15:27.622 --> 15:29.319
-EDDIE, I OWE YOU AN APOLOGY.

15:29.450 --> 15:31.060
I SHOULDN'T HAVE JUST SHOWN
UP AT YOUR TOWER LIKE THAT

15:31.191 --> 15:32.888
WITHOUT TELLING YOU.

15:33.019 --> 15:35.412
-NO, NICOLE. YOU DON'T HAVE
TO APOLOGIZE FOR ANYTHING.

15:36.413 --> 15:38.720
-I JUST WANTED TO
MEET YOU SO MUCH.

15:40.287 --> 15:41.723
AND I'M ASHAMED
OF THE WAY I LOOK.

15:43.943 --> 15:46.075
THAT'S WHY I GOT THE JOB
AT THE ANSWERING SERVICE,

15:47.076 --> 15:48.208
SO NO ONE COULD SEE ME.

15:49.644 --> 15:50.993
I COULD PRETEND TO BE THIN,

15:52.473 --> 15:53.735
PRETEND THAT FOOD
WASN'T THE ONLY THING

15:53.865 --> 15:54.779
I HAD TO COME HOME TO.

15:58.174 --> 16:02.004
SO IF YOU WANNA LEAVE,
I'LL UNDERSTAND.

16:02.874 --> 16:05.877
-LEAVE? HELL NO, I
DON'T WANNA LEAVE.

16:06.008 --> 16:07.705
WE'RE STAYING.

16:07.836 --> 16:10.621
YOU AND I ARE GOING TO INITIATE
THIS RESTAURANT TOGETHER.

16:11.840 --> 16:13.711
-REALLY? ARE YOU SURE?

16:13.842 --> 16:16.105
-ABSOLUTELY. HAVE YOU
EVER KNOWN ME TO LIE?

16:16.714 --> 16:19.761
-NAH. [CHUCKLES]
-NAH.

16:19.891 --> 16:21.589
GARCON!

16:21.719 --> 16:23.199
-[TV ANCHOR] WAS DISCOVERED
THAT THE PRISONERS

16:23.330 --> 16:25.506
HAD ESCAPED FROM TERMINAL
ISLAND EARLY THIS MORNING

16:25.636 --> 16:27.160
AND ARE STILL AT LARGE.

16:27.290 --> 16:28.988
WHILE NOT THOUGHT TO BE
ARMED, THEY ARE DANGEROUS.

16:29.640 --> 16:32.382
AND IN OTHER NEWS, THE
L.A. COUNTY FIRE DEPARTMENT

16:32.513 --> 16:35.429
HEROICALLY EXTINGUISHED AN
OUT OF CONTROL FIRE ON A YACHT

16:35.559 --> 16:38.954
ANCHORED JUST OUTSIDE
CATALINA HARBOR EARLIER TODAY.

16:39.085 --> 16:41.087
ALL ABOARD WERE SAFE
WITH ONLY MINOR INJURIES.

16:41.217 --> 16:42.479
-AND?

16:42.610 --> 16:43.263
-[TV ANCHOR] AND
NOW WITH SPORTS--

16:43.393 --> 16:45.004
-YOU! I KNEW IT!

16:46.570 --> 16:47.876
-SANDY, WAIT!

16:48.007 --> 16:48.790
[DOG BARKS]

16:48.920 --> 16:51.749
-HEY! OH! OH, DOWN, DOWN!

16:51.880 --> 16:53.751
HE'S FILTHY! WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE, HUH?

16:53.882 --> 16:56.102
-I'M SORRY, DAD. HE GOT AWAY
FROM ME AND GOT IN THE MUD.

16:56.232 --> 16:57.625
-GET HIM OUTSIDE AND
GET HIM CLEANED UP.

16:57.755 --> 16:59.105
AND WILL YOU GET
CLEANED UP, TOO?

16:59.235 --> 17:00.541
6YOU GOTTA BE A TIMMY'S
IN A HALF AN HOUR.

17:00.671 --> 17:02.412
KELLY'S ON HER WAY OVER.

17:02.543 --> 17:05.459
I'M TRYING TO HAVE A NICE, QUIET
DINNER IF YOU GET MY DRIFT!

17:05.589 --> 17:06.895
-SURE DO, DAD.
-THANK YOU!

17:07.026 --> 17:07.852
[SMOKE DETECTOR BEEPING]

17:07.983 --> 17:09.202
AH!

17:14.250 --> 17:15.772
[GROANS]

17:22.345 --> 17:23.259
[DOORBELL CHIMES]

17:25.869 --> 17:27.568
AH! DON'T TELL ME.

17:29.135 --> 17:30.919
THIS CAN'T BE, THIS
CAN'T--[CHUCKLES]

17:31.050 --> 17:32.225
OH, IT IS.

17:32.355 --> 17:33.400
HEY!
-HI!

17:34.009 --> 17:34.923
I'M NOT EARLY, AM I?

17:35.054 --> 17:37.143
-NO. GOD, YOU LOOK GREAT.

17:37.273 --> 17:39.623
OH, WATCH OUT. I GOT
A LITTLE MESS HERE.

17:39.754 --> 17:40.798
[LAUGHS]

17:40.929 --> 17:42.583
-HI, HOBIE.
-HI, KELLY.

17:42.713 --> 17:43.975
-OH, WHO'S THIS?

17:44.106 --> 17:45.760
-MY DAD RESCUED
HIM OUTTA THE OCEAN.

17:45.890 --> 17:50.069
-OH! OH, NICE TO
MEET YOU, FELLA.

17:53.115 --> 17:54.812
HE'S CUTE.

17:55.422 --> 17:57.424
-REMEMBER, I'M SPENDING
THE NIGHT AT TIMMY'S.

17:57.554 --> 17:58.468
-YES, I REMEMBER.

17:58.599 --> 18:00.296
-BYE, KELLY.
-BYE.

18:01.254 --> 18:02.081
-SEE YOU LATER, DAD.

18:04.779 --> 18:06.389
OH, HAVE A NICE TIME, GUYS.

18:06.520 --> 18:07.695
-GET OUTTA HERE!

18:07.825 --> 18:09.349
[DOOR SHUTS]

18:10.567 --> 18:12.700
-[CHUCKLES] NICE KID, HUH?

18:12.830 --> 18:14.093
-[LAUGHS]

18:15.137 --> 18:18.706
-NO, NICOLE, YOU HAVE A
LOT OF WONDERFUL QUALITIES

18:18.836 --> 18:20.795
THAT HAVE ABSOLUTELY NOTHING
TO DO WITH YOUR WEIGHT.

18:21.361 --> 18:23.232
-OH YEAH? NAME ONE OR TEN.

18:23.363 --> 18:24.190
[LAUGHS]

18:24.320 --> 18:25.930
-YOUR SENSE OF HUMOR.

18:26.061 --> 18:27.932
AND LET'S NOT FORGET THE
WAY YOU HELP YOUR CLIENTS

18:28.063 --> 18:29.543
WITH ALL THOSE CRAZY MESSAGES.

18:29.673 --> 18:30.761
[LAUGHS]

18:30.892 --> 18:31.849
-AND YOU HAVE A
VERY SEXY LAUGH.

18:32.763 --> 18:34.591
-BUT LOOK AT ME.
-I AM.

18:34.722 --> 18:37.681
AND WHAT I SEE IS A BEAUTIFUL
PERSON WHO HAS A LOT TO OFFER.

18:39.509 --> 18:41.772
NICOLE, IT'S A LOT
EASIER TO FIX THE OUTSIDE

18:41.903 --> 18:43.383
THAN IT IS THE INSIDE.

18:44.297 --> 18:47.561
-EDDIE, I'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT LOSING SOME WEIGHT.

18:48.214 --> 18:51.260
-YOU CAN DO IT,
NICOLE. IF YOU WANT TO.

18:52.174 --> 18:56.178
IT'S UP TO YOU, BUT YOU
CAN ONLY LOSE IT FOR YOU,

18:56.309 --> 18:57.310
NOBODY ELSE.

18:59.225 --> 19:00.661
BUT I KNOW YOU CAN DO IT.

19:02.837 --> 19:04.317
THE POWER IS IN HERE.

19:07.668 --> 19:08.756
I KNOW YOU CAN.

19:13.064 --> 19:13.935
-CHEERS.

19:16.372 --> 19:17.417
[BARKS]

19:20.855 --> 19:23.162
I THINK THE MEAT'S A
LITTLE OVER DONE. I'M SORRY.

19:23.292 --> 19:25.164
-OH, NO. THE
DINNER'S GREAT, MITCH.

19:25.294 --> 19:26.165
-GREAT.

19:27.340 --> 19:29.559
-BUT SANDY DOESN'T
SOUND TOO HAPPY.

19:30.517 --> 19:31.953
WHY DOES HE HAVE TO BE
IN THE LAUNDRY ROOM?

19:32.083 --> 19:33.433
-ARE YOU KIDDING?

19:33.563 --> 19:34.869
LAUNDRY ROOM'S HIS
FAVORITE ROOM, YOU KNOW?

19:34.999 --> 19:38.046
IT'S WARM, COZY.
IT'S NICE IN THERE.

19:38.177 --> 19:39.003
HE LIKES IT IN THERE.

19:39.134 --> 19:40.744
[BARKING]

19:44.487 --> 19:46.010
-MAYBE HE'S HUNGRY.

19:46.141 --> 19:48.883
-YOU'RE RIGHT. LOOK,
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK, OKAY?

19:51.190 --> 19:52.147
PERFECT TIMING.

19:53.235 --> 19:56.064
I HEAR YOU, SWEETHEART, YES.

19:57.457 --> 19:59.198
[BARKS]

19:59.328 --> 20:02.418
SANDY, IF I GIVE YOU THIS JUICY
BONE, WILL YOU JUST CAN IT?

20:03.202 --> 20:04.942
I'M TRYING TO HAVE
A QUIET DINNER HERE.

20:05.073 --> 20:06.117
SHH! SHH!

20:09.643 --> 20:11.253
MMM, GOOD, HMM?

20:11.384 --> 20:15.649
HA HA HA, YOU'RE
RIGHT, HE WAS HUNGRY.

20:17.259 --> 20:19.218
AH. OKAY.

20:20.262 --> 20:21.655
I WOULD LIKE TO MAKE A TOAST.

20:21.785 --> 20:22.830
-OKAY.

20:22.960 --> 20:26.660
-TO YOU, TO US, TO OUR NIGHT.

20:27.269 --> 20:28.705
-CHEERS.
-CHEERS.

20:31.055 --> 20:35.146
[BARKS AND SCRATCHES]

20:37.584 --> 20:38.802
-MAYBE HE'S LONELY.

20:48.203 --> 20:53.164
OH, COME HERE.
COME ON, GOOD BOY.

20:53.817 --> 20:57.256
YES. COME ON. YES.

20:58.822 --> 21:00.781
AWW, THE GOOD BOY.

21:01.303 --> 21:02.870
SEE, MITCH, HE WAS JUST LONELY.

21:03.000 --> 21:03.784
[LAUGHS]

21:03.914 --> 21:04.698
HI, GOOD BOY.

21:04.828 --> 21:05.786
[BARKS]

21:06.526 --> 21:07.788
HE'S AFFECTIONATE, TOO. [LAUGHS]

21:07.918 --> 21:09.529
-YES.

21:09.659 --> 21:12.053
I THINK HE'S HAD ENOUGH
COMPANY FOR TONIGHT, DON'T YOU?

21:12.183 --> 21:13.750
HE'S LOOKS AWFULLY TIRED TO ME.

21:13.881 --> 21:15.317
-OH, YOU THINK SO?
-HE WAS IN THE OCEAN
ALL DAY SWIMMING.

21:15.448 --> 21:16.623
I HAD TO RESCUE HIM.

21:16.753 --> 21:18.581
COME ON. LET'S GET
SOME SLEEP, HUH?

21:18.712 --> 21:19.669
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

21:21.018 --> 21:23.543
LISTEN, SANDY, I
SAVED YOU LIFE, MAN,

21:23.673 --> 21:25.153
AND YOU'RE NOT
SHOWING ANY GRATITUDE.

21:25.284 --> 21:27.851
JUST KEEP A LOW
PROFILE, PLEASE? PLEASE?

21:27.982 --> 21:28.939
[LAUGHS]

21:32.508 --> 21:34.815
WHAT? WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

21:34.945 --> 21:37.905
-SANDY'S LONELY, MITCH. HE
NEEDS YOU MORE THAN I DO.

21:38.035 --> 21:39.950
-HE'S LONELY? HE'S
NOT EVEN MY DOG.

21:40.560 --> 21:41.735
-MITCH, YOU'RE DISTRACTED.

21:41.865 --> 21:43.650
-I'M NOT, I'M NOT.
I'M REALLY NOT.

21:43.780 --> 21:46.914
-SPEND SOME TIME WITH HIM. HE
MUST REALLY MISS HIS MASTER.

21:48.176 --> 21:49.830
WE'LL HAVE OTHER NIGHTS.

21:49.960 --> 21:51.832
[SOFT MOANING]

22:01.145 --> 22:02.016
-TOMORROW NIGHT?

22:03.104 --> 22:04.627
-MY PLACE, 8:00.

22:05.193 --> 22:06.716
[GIGGLES]

22:13.244 --> 22:14.507
-BYE.
-BYE, BYE.

22:16.944 --> 22:18.859
[GROANS]
[BARKS]

22:19.512 --> 22:23.907
THANKS A LOT, DOG! ALPO BREATH!

22:24.038 --> 22:25.996
[BARKING]

22:26.780 --> 22:29.652
OH. OH, MAN.

22:35.876 --> 22:37.051
SHUT UP!

22:37.181 --> 22:40.054
[BARKING]

22:40.968 --> 22:45.581
UH. [SIGHS] 2:00.

22:46.626 --> 22:47.670
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL THING.

22:54.982 --> 22:56.723
THAT'S TWO HOURS
YOU'VE BEEN BARKING.

22:56.853 --> 22:58.377
[BARKS]

22:58.507 --> 22:59.769
I GAVE YOU PIZZA.

23:01.118 --> 23:02.381
I GAVE YOU RICE CAKES.

23:03.991 --> 23:05.949
YOU HAVEN'T EVEN TOUCHED
YOUR RAISIN COOKIES.

23:07.037 --> 23:08.604
WHAT MORE DO YOU WANT FROM ME?

23:08.735 --> 23:10.214
[BARKS]

23:12.956 --> 23:15.306
I WISH YOU COULD TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENED, BUT YOU CAN'T.

23:16.482 --> 23:18.353
I KNOW YOU MISS
YOUR MASTER, SANDY.

23:19.572 --> 23:21.138
AND I KNOW YOUR
NAME'S NOT SANDY.

23:21.922 --> 23:23.532
I'M TELLING YOU,
WE'LL GET YOU HOME.

23:24.185 --> 23:26.492
LIFEGUARDS ARE REALLY
GOOD AT FINDING LOST KIDS.

23:26.622 --> 23:28.407
WE LOSE 'EM ALL THE
TIME, BUT WE FIND 'EM.

23:28.537 --> 23:30.539
I PROMISE YOU, WE'LL
GET YOU TO YOUR MASTER,

23:31.192 --> 23:33.455
BUT RIGHT NOW, I
NEED SOME SLEEP!

23:34.108 --> 23:35.414
[BARKS]

23:35.544 --> 23:36.502
OKAY?

23:37.938 --> 23:40.244
SLEEP. SLEEP.

23:40.375 --> 23:46.033
SHH, SHH! THAT'S GOOD. SHH, SHH!

23:58.175 --> 24:01.440
HMM. TOLD HIM. HMM.

24:11.928 --> 24:13.887
[BARKS]

24:14.017 --> 24:15.192
I SHOULD HAVE LET HIM DROWN.

24:17.368 --> 24:19.370
WHAT IS IT? WHAT DO YOU WANT?

24:20.154 --> 24:21.285
WHAT IS THE STORY?

24:22.286 --> 24:25.420
I SWEAR, IF I HADN'T
JUST SAVED YOUR LIFE,

24:25.551 --> 24:28.249
I'D SWEAR YOU'RE
TRYING TO PISS ME OFF!

24:29.642 --> 24:32.035
AWW, GEES, SANDY.

24:36.170 --> 24:38.172
OH, NO. OH, NO!

24:47.268 --> 24:49.139
I'M GONNA GET YOU, SANDY!

24:49.749 --> 24:52.795
NO! NO!

25:01.282 --> 25:02.588
[GROANS]

25:08.594 --> 25:09.508
-DAD, I'M HOME.

25:25.524 --> 25:27.700
DAD? DAD?

25:30.659 --> 25:31.791
SANDY!

25:38.580 --> 25:40.408
HEY, SANDY. WHERE'S DAD?

25:48.329 --> 25:49.373
[BARKS]

25:51.201 --> 25:52.463
WHAT'S HE DOING IN THERE?

26:05.433 --> 26:06.216
DAD?

26:06.347 --> 26:07.609
-HMM?

26:09.263 --> 26:11.352
AH! OH.

26:12.179 --> 26:14.747
-DAD, I'M SURE HOPING
YOU CAN EXPLAIN THIS.

26:17.314 --> 26:20.535
[LIGHT, INSPIRATIONAL MUSIC]

26:33.374 --> 26:38.074
♪ ALL SUMMER LONG YOU'VE BEEN
♪ RUNNING THROUGH MY MIND

26:40.424 --> 26:45.473
♪ COME AND FIND ME IN MY DREAMS
♪ NO I DON'T LAY AWAKE AT NIGHT

26:48.215 --> 26:52.959
♪ YOU DON'T YOU REALIZE HOW MUCH
♪ A MOMENT MEANS TO ME

26:55.352 --> 27:00.662
♪ YOUR HAND TOUCHING MINE
♪ IT'S LIKE COLLIDING GALAXIES

27:02.664 --> 27:05.275
♪ WHEN I THINK ABOUT YOU

27:05.885 --> 27:08.888
♪ IT MAKES ME SMILE
♪ I THINK I'M GONNA STAY HERE ♪

27:09.018 --> 27:12.587
♪ FOR A WHILE
♪ 'CAUSE WHEN I THINK ABOUT YOU

27:13.196 --> 27:18.114
♪ IT'S DESTINY YOU GOT THE MAGIC
♪ I WANT TO BELIEVE ♪

27:20.247 --> 27:21.727
♪ I'VE FALLING

27:27.515 --> 27:31.780
♪ I'VE FALLING I'VE FALLING

27:33.913 --> 27:36.698
♪ I WANNA STAY HERE WITH MY EYES CLOSED

27:36.829 --> 27:40.006
♪ I CAN SEE I CAN FEEL YOU GOT

27:40.136 --> 27:43.139
♪ YOU GOT ME HERE

27:43.270 --> 27:46.142
♪ WITH MY EYES CLOSED
♪ I CAN SEE I CAN FEEL

27:46.273 --> 27:50.364
♪ YOU GOT...YOU GOT ME

28:13.648 --> 28:16.433
[WAVES CRASH]

28:29.882 --> 28:31.144
[COUGHS]

28:31.274 --> 28:33.668
-IT'S OKAY, NICOLE.
IT'S OKAY, I GOT YOU.

28:33.799 --> 28:34.887
IT'S ALL RIGHT. TAKE IT EASY.

28:37.672 --> 28:40.283
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

28:40.414 --> 28:41.937
-MAN: WE GOT
A BEACHED WHALE HERE?

28:43.939 --> 28:45.114
-ARE YOU OKAY? HUH?

28:45.245 --> 28:46.942
[COUGHING AND CRYING]

28:47.551 --> 28:48.814
-YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY. OKAY?

28:48.944 --> 28:50.424
WE'LL TAKE YOU BACK
TO HEADQUARTERS.

28:50.990 --> 28:52.556
EDDIE, LISTEN.

28:52.687 --> 28:53.688
DARRYL CAN WATCH MY TOWER
WHILE I'M GONE, OKAY?

28:53.819 --> 28:54.689
COME ON.

28:58.084 --> 29:01.391
NICOLE, LISTEN.

29:01.914 --> 29:03.219
SHAUNI'S GOING TO TAKE
CARE OF YOU, OKAY?

29:03.350 --> 29:04.786
I CAN'T LEAVE MY TOWER,

29:04.917 --> 29:05.744
BUT SHE'S GONNA TAKE
REAL GOOD CARE OF YOU.

29:06.222 --> 29:07.702
ALL RIGHT? I'LL
CHECK ON YOU LATER.

29:07.833 --> 29:09.182
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY,
BREAK IT UP!

29:09.312 --> 29:10.618
BREAK IT UP HERE!

29:12.881 --> 29:13.926
I'LL CHECK ON YOU LATER!

29:14.665 --> 29:15.754
[CROWD LAUGHS]

29:15.884 --> 29:18.321
-MAN: SAVE THE WHALE! WHOO!

29:19.061 --> 29:21.194
[TRUCK CRANKS]

29:32.858 --> 29:34.598
-HOWDY. [LAUGHS]

29:34.729 --> 29:36.557
SO THIS IS THE FAMOUS SEA
DOG I'VE HEARD SO MUCH ABOUT.

29:36.687 --> 29:38.298
YOUR PICTURE DOESN'T
DO YOU JUSTICE.

29:38.428 --> 29:41.605
-JUSTICE? REAL JUSTICE
WOULD BE A TRIP TO THE POUND.

29:41.736 --> 29:43.172
-WHAT'S THE MATTER, MITCH?

29:43.303 --> 29:44.086
HAVEN'T YOU AND SANDY
BEEN HITTING IT OFF?

29:44.217 --> 29:44.783
YOU LOOK EXHAUSTED.

29:45.784 --> 29:47.002
-LET'S JUST SAY I WOKE
UP ON THE WRONG SIDE

29:47.133 --> 29:48.134
OF THE DRYER THIS MORNING.

29:48.264 --> 29:49.483
LOOK, DO ME A FAVOR, WILL YA?

29:49.613 --> 29:51.180
TAKE HIM FOR THE
DAY. JUST FOR TODAY.

29:51.311 --> 29:52.747
I'LL OWE YA ONE, OKAY?

29:52.878 --> 29:54.836
-OKAY. MAYBE SOMEBODY
WILL RECOGNIZE HIM.

29:58.144 --> 29:59.449
[TRUCK CRANKS]

30:00.711 --> 30:02.365
[TIRES SQUEAL]

30:04.063 --> 30:05.673
AH, POOR MITCH.

30:05.804 --> 30:06.587
HE DOESN'T KNOW HOW TO HANDLE
A HOUSE GUEST, DOES HE?

30:06.717 --> 30:08.284
RIGHT, BOY? [LAUGHS]

30:08.415 --> 30:10.373
WELL, YOU AND I ARE GOING
TO HAVE A GREAT TIME.

30:10.504 --> 30:11.766
SO HOW ABOUT A WALK
ON THE BEACH, HUH?

30:11.897 --> 30:13.202
SANDY, HEEL.

30:15.901 --> 30:18.164
SANDY! SANDY, GET BACK HERE!

30:22.690 --> 30:25.345
[LIVELY MUSIC BEAT]

30:43.624 --> 30:47.671
[LIVELY MUSIC BEAT]

31:04.340 --> 31:08.127
[LIVELY UPBEAT MUSIC]

31:58.699 --> 32:01.093
NOW, ALL RIGHT, SANDY! I AM
THROUGH MESSING WITH YOU!

32:01.223 --> 32:02.921
NOW, I'M GONNA GIVE YOU
ONE MINUTE PERSONAL TIME

32:03.051 --> 32:04.835
BY THAT TREE OVER THERE,
BUT DON'T YOU GO ANYWHERE!

32:13.932 --> 32:16.499
[BARKS]

32:18.110 --> 32:20.286
-THERE'S NO WAY,
MAN! IT CAN'T BE!

32:20.939 --> 32:24.072
-SANDY! OH! SANDY!

32:25.682 --> 32:26.988
-LET'S GET THE HECK
OUTTA HERE, MAN.

32:27.119 --> 32:28.337
THAT FRIGGING DOG
HAS A COP WITH HIM!

32:29.425 --> 32:32.733
-SANDY! SANDY! GET BACK
HERE, YOU STUPID MUTT!

32:37.912 --> 32:39.174
[BOAT ENGINE CRANKS]

32:41.263 --> 32:42.656
-COME ON! SA--

32:43.918 --> 32:47.182
OH NO, NOT AGAIN!
DOGGONE IT, DOG!

32:48.140 --> 32:50.533
[BARKS]

32:53.406 --> 32:55.669
SANDY, WHAT IS IT, BOY? HUH?

33:03.546 --> 33:05.461
[BARKS]

33:05.592 --> 33:07.420
GIVE ME MITCH AT BAYWATCH
HEADQUARTERS, FAST.

33:07.550 --> 33:08.769
[BARKS]

33:08.899 --> 33:10.031
IT'S ALL RIGHT. IT'S ALL RIGHT.

33:17.038 --> 33:18.561
-YOUR MOUTH'S DRY
AND YOU'RE WEAK,

33:19.214 --> 33:21.216
AND YOU SAY YOU ALMOST FAINTED
AFTER THE FIRST WAVE HIT YOU.

33:24.089 --> 33:25.481
ARE YOU TAKING
DIET PILLS, NICOLE?

33:33.402 --> 33:34.273
YEAH.

33:36.449 --> 33:37.667
HAVE YOU EATEN ANYTHING TODAY?

33:38.755 --> 33:40.061
-JUST SAND AND SALTWATER.

33:40.192 --> 33:41.802
-HEY, THIS ISN'T A JOKE!

33:42.324 --> 33:44.718
BY TAKING THOSE DIET PILLS
AND LAYING OUT IN THE SUN

33:44.848 --> 33:46.328
WITH NO FOOD IN YOUR SYSTEM,

33:46.459 --> 33:48.287
YOU COULD'VE BEEN
REALLY SERIOUSLY HURT.

33:49.766 --> 33:51.290
-SERIOUSLY HURT?

33:53.074 --> 33:57.035
I'VE SPENT MY ENTIRE LIFE
BEING SERIOUSLY HURT!

33:57.948 --> 33:59.950
HURT BY JOKES AT MY EXPENSE!

34:01.300 --> 34:02.388
YOU HEARD THEM OUT THERE.

34:03.389 --> 34:05.695
I'VE ALWAYS HATED
GIRLS LIKE YOU.

34:05.826 --> 34:09.960
THIN AND BEAUTIFUL.
EVERYTHING COMING SO EASY.

34:10.657 --> 34:14.661
CHEERLEADING AND DATES.
CLOTHES THAT FIT.

34:15.966 --> 34:18.317
I CAN'T TELL YOU HOW MAY
CRASH DIETS I'VE TRIED.

34:18.447 --> 34:21.275
HOW MANY TIMES
I'VE LOST 20 POUNDS

34:22.277 --> 34:23.800
ONLY TO GAIN 30 BACK.

34:25.976 --> 34:27.848
A PERSON CAN BE CALLED LARD BUTT

34:27.978 --> 34:29.719
ONLY SO MANY TIMES WITHOUT--

34:32.286 --> 34:35.899
DO YOU KNOW WHAT CLASS I DREADED
ALL DURING SCHOOL, SHAUNI?

34:37.510 --> 34:42.254
NOT HISTORY OR
BIOLOGY OR ALGEBRA.

34:43.429 --> 34:45.866
GYM CLASS. [CHUCKLES]

34:48.172 --> 34:51.306
PUTTING ON THOSE SHORTS FOR
EVERYONE TO SEE AND LAUGH AT.

34:55.179 --> 34:56.659
YOU KNOW WHAT I
REALIZE NOW, SHAUNI?

34:58.792 --> 35:00.837
IT'S NOT EVEN THE GIRLS
LIKE YOU THAT I HATE.

35:04.580 --> 35:07.105
IT'S ME. [CRIES]

35:07.670 --> 35:09.759
I HATE MYSELF.

35:18.116 --> 35:20.205
-I CAN RELATE TO THAT
SELF HATRED, NICOLE.

35:27.647 --> 35:28.561
AND YOU'RE RIGHT.

35:30.084 --> 35:31.912
I WAS A CHEERLEADING
IN HIGHSCHOOL,

35:33.522 --> 35:35.742
AND I HAD GREAT CLOTHES
AND LOTS OF DATES.

35:37.918 --> 35:39.137
LOTS OF DATES.

35:40.529 --> 35:41.400
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

35:42.749 --> 35:45.273
I NEVER KNEW IF THOSE
GUYS LIKE ME FOR ME,

35:46.535 --> 35:48.058
OR FOR WHO THEY
THOUGHT THAT I WAS

35:48.189 --> 35:49.451
BECAUSE OF THE WAY I LOOKED.

35:50.148 --> 35:53.151
IT WAS AS IF IT DIDN'T
MATTER THAT I HAD A HEART,

35:53.977 --> 35:55.762
AND FEELINGS AND A BRAIN.

35:55.892 --> 35:57.067
IT DIDN'T MATTER AT ALL.

35:57.851 --> 36:00.245
BECAUSE THEY NEVER
ASKED ME MY OPINION.

36:01.115 --> 36:03.683
AND IF I GAVE IT, ANYWAY,
THEY NEVER LISTENED.

36:04.249 --> 36:05.163
AND THAT HURT.

36:06.773 --> 36:08.688
THEY DIDN'T BOTHER TO
LOOK DEEPER INTO ME.

36:10.429 --> 36:12.518
AND I GUESS FOR A WHILE,
I QUIT LOOKIN', TOO.

36:15.085 --> 36:18.741
AND I DID A LOT OF THINGS THAT
I AM NOT PROUD OF, NICOLE.

36:20.482 --> 36:21.918
AND I HATED MYSELF.

36:26.401 --> 36:29.491
BUT THEN I MET SOMEONE
WHO BELIEVED IN ME.

36:30.231 --> 36:32.755
IN ME, FOR WHO I
AM ON THE INSIDE.

36:34.627 --> 36:36.455
AND HE HELPED ME
BELIEVE IN MYSELF.

36:36.585 --> 36:39.893
AND NICOLE, LIKING WHO YOU ARE
ON THE INSIDE IS EVERYTHING.

36:44.463 --> 36:45.942
-IS THAT PERSON EDDIE?

36:47.466 --> 36:48.293
-YEAH.

36:52.558 --> 36:54.168
-HE'S A REALLY TERRIFIC GUY.

36:56.039 --> 36:58.346
I'VE NEVER FELT SO LIKED,

36:58.999 --> 37:01.131
SO MUCH ACCEPTANCE
IN MY ENTIRE LIFE.

37:06.006 --> 37:07.747
HE'S A HUNK. [LAUGHS]

37:08.313 --> 37:09.357
HE IS.

37:09.923 --> 37:11.359
-YEAH.

37:11.490 --> 37:12.969
-BUT, UH, WHAT HE'S
GOT ON THE INSIDE,

37:13.100 --> 37:14.449
CUTE COULD NEVER TOUCH.

37:15.972 --> 37:17.235
-HE'S MY BEST FRIEND.

37:17.844 --> 37:19.062
-HE'S MINE, TOO.

37:22.065 --> 37:23.197
[SNIFFLES]

37:33.990 --> 37:35.340
-I TRACED THE BOAT
THEY TOOK OFF ON.

37:35.470 --> 37:36.776
IT BELONGS TO A TILLY MCKAY.

37:36.906 --> 37:38.343
SHE HASN'T BEEN
SEEN IN THREE DAYS.

37:38.473 --> 37:40.170
-WHERE WERE THEY HEADED?

37:40.301 --> 37:41.215
-THEY HEADED SOUTH. WE'RE
GONNA HAVE TO MOVE TO CATCH 'EM.

37:41.346 --> 37:42.956
-COME ON, SANDY, COME ON! YEAH!

37:43.826 --> 37:45.088
ALL RIGHT, I'VE
GOT IT. LET'S GO!

37:47.221 --> 37:48.091
HIT IT.

37:57.449 --> 38:01.279
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

38:11.201 --> 38:12.464
-SLOW DOWN,
THAT'S THE BOAT.

38:12.594 --> 38:13.900
-YOU SURE?
-YEAH.

38:16.032 --> 38:17.512
[SIREN BEEPS]

38:23.213 --> 38:24.780
[GUN FIRES]

38:29.568 --> 38:30.960
-GET ME AS CLOSE
AS YOU CAN, HUH?

38:33.136 --> 38:35.313
[GUN FIRES]

38:39.012 --> 38:41.014
[GUN FIRES]

38:46.367 --> 38:49.327
[GUN FIRES]

39:03.341 --> 39:04.733
[MEN GRUNTING]

39:15.091 --> 39:16.223
[BARKING]

39:20.532 --> 39:21.837
-YOU ALL RIGHT, MITCH?
-YEAH.

39:22.403 --> 39:23.796
-NOW THERE'S A MAN

39:23.926 --> 39:24.927
WHO DEFINITELY HAS A
RIGHT TO REMAIN SILENT.

39:25.058 --> 39:26.189
GOOD BOY.
-GOOD BOY.

39:28.453 --> 39:29.367
WHERE YOU GOING?

39:34.894 --> 39:36.243
[WHIMPERS]

39:37.723 --> 39:39.289
OKAY, PAL. OKAY.

39:40.334 --> 39:43.816
-OH! OH, HENRY! HENRY,
I THOUGHT YOU'D NEVER--

39:43.946 --> 39:45.208
-HENRY!

39:45.339 --> 39:47.123
-HOW'D YOU EVER
FIND ME, YOUNG MAN?

39:47.254 --> 39:48.560
SO THAT'S YOUR NAME. HENRY.

39:48.690 --> 39:49.778
-YES! THIS IS MY DOG.

39:55.131 --> 39:56.742
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

39:58.483 --> 40:00.354
-I'M GONNA FIX YOU
A SPECIAL DINNER

40:00.485 --> 40:02.269
FOR SAVING HENRY AND ME.

40:02.400 --> 40:03.792
-WELL, ACTUALLY, I WOULD LOVE
TO STAY, BUT I REALLY CAN'T.

40:03.923 --> 40:04.706
YOU SEE, I GOT A DATE.

40:04.837 --> 40:06.708
-OH, WE WOULDN'T HEAR OF IT!

40:06.839 --> 40:08.231
WE AIN'T HAD SUCH A FINE
LOOKING YOUNG MAN IN OUR BOAT

40:08.362 --> 40:09.450
IN A MONTH OF SUNDAYS.

40:09.581 --> 40:11.321
-[LAUGHS] MAYBE
SOME OTHER TIME, HUH?

40:11.452 --> 40:12.627
[BARKS]

40:13.280 --> 40:17.023
-NO, NO. I'M GONNA FIX
YOU SOME WHISKEY STEW.

40:17.153 --> 40:18.938
IT STICKS TO THE RIBS, BOY.

40:19.068 --> 40:20.679
-OH!

40:20.809 --> 40:21.810
[LAUGHS]

40:21.941 --> 40:22.811
-WELL, UH,

40:24.726 --> 40:27.294
ACTUALLY, I'D LOVE TO STAY.

40:27.425 --> 40:29.514
-YEAH. WELL, I'LL
START SUPPER. [GIGGLES]

40:29.644 --> 40:31.777
[BARKING]
[GROANS]

40:42.483 --> 40:44.964
-WELL, THERE YOU GO,
GEORGE. NICE, CLEAN TANK.

40:45.094 --> 40:47.140
AND GRACIE, I HOPE YOU
APPROVE OF THE NEW DECOR.

40:55.888 --> 40:56.889
[KNOCKS]

40:58.586 --> 40:59.457
HI.

41:00.109 --> 41:00.980
-CAN I COME IN?

41:01.894 --> 41:03.373
-YEAH, SURE.

41:10.990 --> 41:12.165
-EDDIE, I'M REALLY SORRY.

41:13.427 --> 41:14.689
I HOPE YOU CAN FORGIVE ME.

41:15.647 --> 41:18.476
UM, I'VE BEEN DOING
A LOT OF THINKING,

41:19.259 --> 41:20.260
AND YOU'RE RIGHT.

41:20.782 --> 41:23.698
I HAVE BEEN MONOPOLIZING
OUR TIME WITH MY PLANS.

41:25.657 --> 41:27.963
BUT I, I BROUGHT
A PEACE OFFERING.

41:31.489 --> 41:34.666
DODGER TICKETS, RIGHT
BEHIND THE DUGOUT, TONIGHT.

41:36.058 --> 41:37.190
-YOU GOTTA BE KIDDING ME!

41:38.800 --> 41:40.846
SHAUNI, THESE THINGS
ARE IMPOSSIBLE TO GET.

41:42.804 --> 41:44.110
WAIT A MINUTE, IT'S
SATURDAY NIGHT.

41:44.240 --> 41:45.720
WHAT ABOUT YOUR
PARENTS, THE CLUB?

41:45.851 --> 41:48.070
-I TOLD MY PARENTS
THAT I HAVE SOMETHING

41:48.201 --> 41:51.683
FAR MORE IMPORTANT TO DO WITH
SOMEBODY VERY IMPORTANT TO ME.

41:53.859 --> 41:55.295
I MISSED YOU SO MUCH.

41:58.124 --> 41:59.212
-I MISSED YOU, TOO.

42:09.657 --> 42:13.182
LISTEN, WOULD YOU MIND IF
WE GOT THERE A LITTLE LATE?

42:13.879 --> 42:16.969
-NO. WOULD YOU MIND IF
WE LEFT A LITTLE EARLY?

42:19.232 --> 42:21.016
-WHY WOULD WE
LEAVE A LITTLE EARLY

42:21.147 --> 42:22.452
IF WE'RE GONNA GET THERE LATE?

42:23.018 --> 42:24.498
-FOR THE SAME REASON THAT
WE'RE GOING TO GET THERE LATE.

42:27.153 --> 42:28.328
-SAY GOODNIGHT, GRACIE.

42:40.819 --> 42:43.561
[END THEME PLAYS]
